274
00:24:21,962 --> 00:24:24,909
[SPEAKER_07]: Is that year two, year three, year four?

275
00:24:25,971 --> 00:24:29,037
[SPEAKER_07]: The early years, first two years at least.

276
00:24:29,422 --> 00:24:31,044
[SPEAKER_07]: So not in the first two years.

277
00:24:31,565 --> 00:24:36,470
[SPEAKER_07]: I want to deliver a capital investment programme for the whole of the UK.

278
00:24:36,490 --> 00:24:37,091
[SPEAKER_07]: No, no, I heard that.

279
00:24:37,111 --> 00:24:38,052
[SPEAKER_07]: I heard that very clearly.

280
00:24:38,072 --> 00:24:40,515
[SPEAKER_07]: And that will be our focus.

281
00:24:40,755 --> 00:24:44,880
[SPEAKER_07]: And so it will not be in the early part of the new Parliament.

282
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,142
[SPEAKER_07]: So not in the first two years.

283
00:24:47,083 --> 00:24:49,265
[SPEAKER_44]: So certainly not 2020, as Nicola Sturgeon wants.

284
00:24:49,285 --> 00:24:50,687
[SPEAKER_44]: Yes, there's a man there in the black shirt.

285
00:24:52,034 --> 00:24:53,357
[SPEAKER_44]: Yes, actually, both got black shirts.

286
00:24:53,377 --> 00:24:54,119
[SPEAKER_44]: I was very confused.

287
00:24:54,139 --> 00:24:55,202
[SPEAKER_44]: Yes, in the black T-shirt.

288
00:24:56,947 --> 00:25:02,601
[SPEAKER_45]: So what gives it your right to be your priority if it's a priority of the Scottish people?

289
00:25:06,648 --> 00:25:12,296
[SPEAKER_07]: There are elections in Scotland in 2021, and obviously an expression will come from that.

290
00:25:12,757 --> 00:25:33,448
[SPEAKER_07]: It is, I think, our right as a party to put forward a programme for the whole of the UK, and that is what we're doing, an investment strategy for the whole of the UK, and point out, I point out, that Scotland will get 100 billion of investment under a Labour government which will make a very significant difference to the lives of people all across Scotland.

291
00:25:33,729 --> 00:25:35,912
[SPEAKER_07]: That, I'm sure, is something you would welcome.

292
00:25:35,892 --> 00:25:40,333
[SPEAKER_45]: Jeremy, there's already a mandate from Scottish people to have another referendum.

293
00:25:41,479 --> 00:25:42,865
[SPEAKER_45]: Well, there is actually.

294
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:53,551
[SPEAKER_45]: There is a mandate from the last Scottish parliamentary elections and Scottish people have voted for that mandate.

295
00:25:53,852 --> 00:26:00,099
